main event: A civilian reported observing a large, gas-like object setting in the western sky in Falls Church, Virginia for 20 minutes on 14 December 1964.
interesting points: The object was sharply outlined and appeared to fade out in sections., The witness did not expect the object and was surprised by its sudden appearance., The object was observed setting just above the trees to the southeast., The observation was identified as consistent with the setting moon due to atmospheric refraction., No physical details were discerned due to distortion from atmospheric conditions.
